        <h2 class="title"><a href="/news-burning-man-burns-monday">News: Burning Man burns on Monday</a></h2>    <span class="submitted">Submitted by <a href="/user/brad" title="View user profile." rel="nofollow">brad</a> on Tue, 2007-08-28 04:28.</span>
    <span class="taxonomy"><ul class="links inline"><li class="first taxonomy_term_86"><a href="/topic/burning-man" rel="tag" title="About burning man, my other home" class="taxonomy_term_86 active">Burning Man</a></li>
<li class="last taxonomy_term_1"><a href="/archives/cat_photography.html" rel="tag" title="" class="taxonomy_term_1">Photography</a></li>
</ul></span>
    <div class="content"><p>Update:  I now have a whole <a href="/topic/burning-man">Burning Man</a> area on the blog!</p>

<p>I&#8217;ve not been blogging of late because I&#8217;m at Burning Man, and while normally I don&#8217;t report breaking news in this blog, we just witnessed a strange event.  Through accident or arson, the Man was set alight this evening shortly after totality began in the eclipse of the moon.</p>

<p>The man was not loaded with explosives or fireworks as he is before his planned burn, so it was a more sedate affair, and soon fire crews arrived to &#8220;save the man&#8221; &#8212; something we have been asking for in mock protests for years.   They did put him out, and he still stands, a bit worse for wear.</p>

<p>I managed to get some photos of the burn&#8230;.</p>

<p><img src=http://www.templetons.com/images/drip-flame.jpg></p>

<p>Efforts to save the man&#8230;</p>

<p><img src=http://www.templetons.com/images/save-the-man.jpg></p>

<p>The injured man, missing a hand and burnt, under the eclipsed moon&#8230;</p>

<p><img src=http://www.templetons.com/images/man-moon-small.jpg></p>
</div>
    <div class="links">&raquo; <ul class="links inline"><li class="first blog_usernames_blog"><a href="/blog/brad" title="Read brad&#039;s latest blog entries." class="blog_usernames_blog">brad&#039;s blog</a></li>
